metadata.name: Morixels Mans #157
metadata.description:
The Morixels Mans is unique Random Generated 10,000 PFP NFTs, and this collection is for people like me who are nostalgic for pixel arts.
This collection is manually designed.
The original Artwork was designed in 24 by 24 pixels and then resized to 1080 by 1080 resolution. 
The number of Traits in this collection is 12 (120 layers) and it has the ability to make 31,091,558,400 NFTs.
Some ‚Äãlayers are less than 1 percent of the total, some 100 percent, and some between 0.1 and 100 percent.
To create balance, these NFTs are randomly minted, and this is a chance for everyone to get a rare version. So due to the low price of these NFTs, if the rare version did not belong to you, it is still possible for you to mint the new NFTs.
To Produce this collection, all the layers were designed pixel by pixel, which was time-consuming and difficult. And this greatly increases the value of this collection.

Because this is an NFT in PFP format, you can put it on your avatar on Twitter or Instagram.

Twitter: @Morixels

Website: https://morixels.com/

Designed by: @morteza_yousefy
Made in 2022

metadata.name: Swatches #126
metadata.description:
Swatches is the first generative token project by Paul Drzal.

Like photography gels scattered on the light table, the layers combine to create the composition.  A random four-color palette in varying opacities creates your swatch, hand pulled on the screen.

Colors are inspired by the bold stylized drawings of architects Wes Jones and Neil Denari.

Press ‚Äòs‚Äô to save your Swatch.  Zoom out and refresh to save a larger file.

metadata.name: Sunset in Paradise #241
metadata.description:
Hundreds of Walkers descend the screen drawing a sky, sea and the sun reflection; creating a twilight scene of a sunset or possibly a sunrise depending on which coast your paradise can be found. 
Features - 32 Palettes 
5 Possible background colors per palette
3 different complexities of sky:
	-Refined - 3 colors (25% chance)
	-Complex - 5 colors (25% chance)
	-Normal - 4 colors (50% chance)
2 possible border colors: 
	Matching the sun color (40% chance) 
	Matching the sea color (60% chance)
2 different stroke thickness: 
	Fine (25% chance) 
	Medium-point (75% chance) 
Different amounts of Walkers for Sky, Sea and reflection.

Made by @p1x3lboy in p5.js
June 2022

metadata.name: block-sekai #8
metadata.description:
Rules:
- A block is made up of a simple rectangle shape and a tiny rectangle inside of it.
- Use a grid-like system to distribute blocks from top to bottom, from left to right, but not strictly follow the grid.
- Each block has random size. The maximum width and maximum height of block and the distance between adjacent blocks are randomly generated before the distribution.
- The distribution model produces varying results in rotation and spacing.
- For each block, it projects another rectangle with random size and rotation at the background, which extends its length to the bottom of the painting.
- There are lines behind the block which connect all of them together.
- Random patterns.

Created by Costa C. | OneRocket.nft

metadata.name: KOSMISCH #3
metadata.description:
Partying in outer space!

This work is best experienced as a huge printed poster while listening to Sun Ra. 

Press 's' to save a frame.
Press 'm' to generate a medium sized (3000x4200) PNG
Press 'l' to generate a large (4500x6300) PNG
Press 'x' to generate an extra large (6000x8400) PNG

Please note: Generating the larger PNGs does not work with all browsers. Successfully tested with Microsoft Edge on macOS, though.
